div.p:
The problem can be considered in terms of four of its aspects:
An international agreement not to conduct further tests as a part of a disarmament program;
An international agreement as a means of avoiding the successful development of thermonuclear weapons by either side;
The desirability of a test before the United States is prepared to produce weapons and at a time when any successful test in the thermonuclear field may have a significant effect on Soviet decisions;
The effect of the Presidential election on the decision to proceed with a test in December.
